S4. Known-groups validity

dat_long = dat %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(UCLA3_TOT, UCLA20_TOT),
               names_to = "scale",
               values_to = "values")
cor_marit_U3 = broom::tidy(cor.test(~as.numeric(Marital_status) + UCLA3_TOT, dat))
                          
cor_marit_U20 = broom::tidy(cor.test(~as.numeric(Marital_status) + UCLA20_TOT, dat))

res_rpb = rbind(cor_marit_U3, cor_marit_U20)
  
rb = metaConvert::es_from_pt_bis_r(
  pt_bis_r = res_rpb$estimate, 
  n_exp = rep(sum(dat$Marital_status == "Couple"),2),
  n_nexp = rep(sum(dat$Marital_status == "Single"),2))
rb = rb %>% select(starts_with("r") | starts_with("d"))
rb$estimate = rb$r
rb$se = rb$r_se
rb$pred = c("UCLA3_TOT", "UCLA20_TOT")
rb$group = "Convergent validity"
rb$out = "Marital status"
rb

S5. Convergent validity

PHQ-9

lm_phq = lm(PHQ_TOT ~ UCLA3_TOT + UCLA20_TOT, dat)
regrOut <- calc.yhat(lm_phq)

boot.out <- boot(dat,
                 boot.yhat, 10,
                 lmOut=lm_phq,
                 regrout0=regrOut)
result <- booteval.yhat(regrOut, boot.out, bty="perc")

res_plot1 = data.frame(regrOut$PredictorMetrics[-nrow(regrOut$PredictorMetrics),])[,cols] %>%
  pivot_longer(cols=everything(),
               values_to="values",
               names_to="variance") %>%
  mutate(scale = rep(c("UCLA-LS-3", "UCLA-LS-20"), each=3))
res_plot1.lo = data.frame(result$lowerCIpm)[,cols] %>%
  pivot_longer(cols=everything(),
               values_to="values",
               names_to="variance") %>%
  mutate(scale = rep(c("UCLA-LS-3", "UCLA-LS-20"), each=3))
names(res_plot1.lo) = paste0(names(res_plot1.lo), "_ci_lo")
res_plot1.up = data.frame(result$upperCIpm)[,cols] %>%
  pivot_longer(cols=everything(),
               values_to="values",
               names_to="variance")%>%
  mutate(scale = rep(c("UCLA-LS-3", "UCLA-LS-20"), each=3))
names(res_plot1.up) = paste0(names(res_plot1.up), "_ci_up")
res_plot1 = cbind(res_plot1, res_plot1.lo, res_plot1.up)

res_plot1$variance[res_plot1$variance =="CD.0"] <- "Total\n(unique+common)"

ggplot(res_plot1, aes(x=variance, y = values)) + 
    geom_point() +
    facet_wrap(~scale) + 
    theme_bw() + 
    geom_errorbar(aes(ymin=values_ci_lo, ymax=values_ci_up), width=.2,
                  position=position_dodge(.9))

Nomological net

predictors = c("UCLA3_TOT", "UCLA20_TOT")
outcomes = c("PHQ_TOT","GAD_TOT",
             "Age_dim", "Financ_diff")
res = NULL
for (pred in predictors) {
  for (out in outcomes) {
    res_cor = NA
    res_cor = cbind(pred, out,
        broom::tidy(
          cor.test(~ dat[, pred] + dat[, out])))
    res = rbind(res, res_cor)
  }
}
res$se = (res$conf.high - res$conf.low) / qnorm(.975)
# res$name = paste0(res$pred, "_", res$out)
res$group = ifelse(res$out %in% c("PHQ_TOT", "GAD_TOT"), "Convergent validity", "Discriminant validity")
resplot = res
# resplot = dplyr::bind_rows(res, rb)
# resplot = data.frame(resplot[,intersect(names(res), names(rb))])
resplot$name = resplot$out


forestplot(
  resplot,
  colour = pred,
  estimate = estimate,
  se = se,
  xlab = "Association of the UCLA-3/UCLA-20\n with various variables") +
  ggforce::facet_col(
    facets = ~group,
    scales = "free_y",
    space = "free"
  )

      assign(paste0("SENS_SEV_", suffix), round(with(subset(dat, dat[, paste0("UCLA20_DIAG_", suffix, "txt")] == "yes"), sum(UCLA3_DIAG_SEV)/length(UCLA3_DIAG_SEV)), 4)*100)
